<tech_fingerprinter_guide>
<title>TECHNOLOGY FINGERPRINTING</title>

<critical>Technology fingerprinting is the foundation of attack surface mapping. Identifying the exact technology stack, versions, and configurations reveals potential vulnerabilities, known CVEs, and framework-specific attack vectors. Accurate fingerprinting transforms generic testing into targeted exploitation.</critical>

<scope>
- Web server identification (nginx, Apache, IIS, Kestrel, etc.)
- Framework detection (Django, Rails, Express, Next.js, etc.)
- CMS fingerprinting (WordPress, Drupal, Joomla, etc.)
- JavaScript library detection and version enumeration
- Backend language identification (PHP, Python, Java, Node.js, etc.)
- Database technology inference
- Cloud platform and CDN detection
- API technology identification (GraphQL, REST, gRPC)
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Collect HTTP response headers from multiple endpoints.
2. Analyze Set-Cookie patterns for framework signatures.
3. Examine response body for technology-specific patterns.
4. Trigger error conditions to reveal stack traces.
5. Check common framework-specific paths (/admin, /wp-admin, /graphql).
6. Analyze JavaScript includes for library versions.
7. Cross-reference findings for confidence scoring.
8. Map technologies to known CVEs and attack vectors.
</methodology>

<fingerprinting_techniques>
<header_analysis>
{% raw %}
# Key headers revealing technology stack
Server: nginx/1.21.0              # Web server + version
X-Powered-By: PHP/8.1.0           # Language + version
X-AspNet-Version: 4.0.30319       # .NET version
X-Generator: Drupal 9             # CMS identification
X-Drupal-Cache: HIT               # Drupal-specific
X-Vercel-Id: iad1::xxxxx          # Platform (Vercel)

# Cloud provider indicators
X-Amz-Cf-Id: xxxxx                # AWS CloudFront
X-Azure-Ref: xxxxx                # Azure
X-Goog-*: xxxxx                   # Google Cloud
CF-Ray: xxxxx                     # Cloudflare
{% endraw %}
</header_analysis>

<cookie_fingerprints>
{% raw %}
# Session cookie patterns reveal frameworks
PHPSESSID=xxx           # PHP
JSESSIONID=xxx          # Java (Servlet/JSP)
ASP.NET_SessionId=xxx   # ASP.NET
_rails_session=xxx      # Ruby on Rails
laravel_session=xxx     # Laravel
django_session=xxx      # Django
connect.sid=xxx         # Express.js
next-auth.session=xxx   # NextAuth.js
__cfduid=xxx            # Cloudflare

# Authentication cookies
wp-settings-xxx         # WordPress logged in
Drupal.visitor=xxx      # Drupal
{% endraw %}
</cookie_fingerprints>

<body_patterns>
{% raw %}
# CMS signatures in HTML
wp-content/              # WordPress
/sites/default/files/    # Drupal
/media/system/           # Joomla
/typo3/                  # TYPO3

# Framework signatures
data-reactroot           # React
ng-version               # Angular
__NEXT_DATA__            # Next.js
__nuxt                   # Nuxt.js
data-v-[a-f0-9]          # Vue.js
